[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-14T16:59:22+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from Pok\u00e9mon Sword / Pok\u00e9mon Shield\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/D9l4JLyvyr5Ld36kEkTLMPUCCtM=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73653220/Switch_PokemonSwordPokemonShield_ExpansionPass_screen_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"J6rMOi\">Hackers released a collection of leaked data from Pok\u00e9mon game developer Game Freak over the weekend, including personal information about employees. Game Freak \u2014 which develops the main lineup of <em>Pok\u00e9mon</em> video games \u2014 <a href=\"https://www.gamefreak.co.jp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/info20241010.pdf\">confirmed the breach</a> in a statement, saying (per a machine translation from Japanese) that it was the result of \u201cunauthorized access to our servers by a third party\u201d and dated back to August of 2024.</p>\n<p id=\"tCtz5j\">Game Freak said the leaked personal information \u2014 which it characterizes as names ", "id": 1324110, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/14/24270226/pokemon-game-freak-data-leak-confirmed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon developer faces major data leak", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-14T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Neva.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/87EkasVS0ZpTjNebXzeFyCfx0AQ=/283x0:3523x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73652581/Neva_13.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Devolver Digital</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap\" id=\"OgUqpM\">After the launch of <em>Gris</em>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/12/13/18137844/gris-review-nintendo-switch-pc-gaming\">a beautiful game exploring grief</a>, the team at Nomada Studio in Barcelona needed a long break. They spent around half a year not even thinking about what was next, avoiding words like \u201cUnity\u201d or \u201csequel.\u201d Eventually, director Conrad Roset, who became a parent during that time, came up with the idea of a similar experience that would introduce a new companion, allowing players to connect with and care for another character.</p>\n<p id=\"7RLfI3\">\u201cI told him, no problem, as long as it\u2019s not a four-legged animal, you can d", "id": 1322351, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24267805/neva-nomada-studio-interview-gris-devolver", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The stunning indie game Gris now has a beautiful follow-up about love and loss", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-14T10:44:50+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Microsoft Holds Its Xbox 2016 Briefing During Annual E3 Gaming Conference\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uDqpISnkMsiHMjfvInMJDzDgaVo=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73652411/539996718.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Kevork Djansezian/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fTQ123\">Microsoft is promoting Rare studio lead Craig Duncan to the head of Xbox Game Studios, following the retirement of 